headline: Should You Forget Ultra-High-Yield Altria? Here's Why These Unstoppable Stocks Are Better Buys.
summary: Altria (NYSE: MO) as a stock, is not all that attractive for investors.  The main thing about Altria that's likely attracting investors is its ultra-high 7% dividend yield and the fact that the dividend has risen with each passing year for several decades now.  Investors interested in dividends (and getting a high yield) might be better off looking at stocks like Realty Income (NYSE: O) or Vici Properties (NYSE: Vici), which have yields of 5.6% and 5.4%, respectively.
